    "caption": "Climbs where nothing else dares, eats almost everything.",
    "shortDescription": "Mountain goats can scale near-vertical cliff faces because their hooves have two toes that spread wide for balance plus a hard outer edge and a soft rubbery inner pad that grips rock like a climbing shoe. Their rectangular pupils give them a very wide field of vision to watch for predators from any angle. Fun fact: Goats have accents — studies show that young goats develop slightly different calls depending on which social group they grow up in."
